(IN DISTINCT YELLING)

49:03.120 --> 49:05.771
John!
- You have no bloody right, Tommy!

49:05.840 --> 49:08.161
Shh. Shh. Listen to me! Listen to me!

49:09.920 --> 49:13.083
A girl who needs a husband,
a man who needs a wife.

49:14.760 --> 49:19.288
Tom, I'm not bloody marrying some
fucking mushroom picker..

49:19.480 --> 49:21.562
Shh,john boy. Come on, listen.

49:23.600 --> 49:24.806
I've already betrothed you.

49:26.080 --> 49:29.289
So if you back out now, there's going
to be one fucking mighty war

49:29.560 --> 49:31.130
breaking out here that's
going to make the Somme...

49:31.240 --> 49:34.289
That's going to make the Somme
look like a fucking tea party.

49:34.640 --> 49:36.165
But if you marry her,

49:36.880 --> 49:39.087
our family and the Lee family

49:39.240 --> 49:40.890
will be united forever

49:40.960 --> 49:42.371
and this war will be over.

49:42.440 --> 49:43.885
Now, it's up to you, john.

49:44.800 --> 49:45.801
War

49:47.360 --> 49:48.361
or peace?

49:51.280 --> 49:52.406
Let go of me!

50:05.920 --> 50:07.206
Right.

50:07.280 --> 50:09.601
You should see the size of her dowry.

50:10.640 --> 50:11.641
Her what?

50:12.520 --> 50:13.965
Her dad's giving you a car.

50:21.400 --> 50:22.481
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

50:23.520 --> 50:24.521
Will he do?

50:31.080 --> 50:32.081
He'll do.

50:32.200 --> 50:33.804
(ALL CHEERING)

50:40.440 --> 50:41.441
Here she is.

50:41.560 --> 50:42.800
JOHN: She'd better be under 50.

50:43.880 --> 50:44.881
Come here.

50:46.000 --> 50:47.001
Go on.

50:55.600 --> 50:58.046
PRIEST: We're here today to
join in matrimony,

50:58.560 --> 51:01.006
this man and this woman...

51:02.680 --> 51:03.920
You look well.

51:04.920 --> 51:06.968
PRIEST: And harmony and togetherness

51:09.720 --> 51:12.326
which is sanctioned and honoured
by the presence and the power

51:12.400 --> 51:14.209
of these two families around us.

51:17.080 --> 51:19.447
Do you, john Michael Shelby,

51:19.680 --> 51:22.286
take Esme Martha Lee to be your
beautiful young wife?

51:22.360 --> 51:23.486
You got my invitation?

51:24.120 --> 51:26.009
Grace said there's a truce.

51:27.200 --> 51:28.326
Family day.

51:30.640 --> 51:31.971
Your husband couldn't make it?

51:32.400 --> 51:34.050
He's not speaking to me.

51:34.560 --> 51:37.166
And when he does he calls me a
"Fucking Shelby"

51:37.240 --> 51:39.004
even though I'm a Thorne now.

51:39.120 --> 51:40.724
A thorn in my side, that's for sure.

51:43.840 --> 51:45.490
My God, Tommy,

51:46.360 --> 51:48.249
you admire him, don't you?

51:48.320 --> 51:50.527
PRIEST: There remains
one more part of the ceremony.

51:50.800 --> 51:52.245
It's the mingling of the two bloods.

51:54.480 --> 51:57.290
So the two families
become the one family.

52:00.400 --> 52:01.925
I now pronounce you man and wife!

52:02.000 --> 52:03.047
(ALL CHEERING)

52:03.120 --> 52:05.088
MAN: Well, john, kiss the bride,
will you?

52:08.440 --> 52:11.603
(ALL CHEERING)

52:14.280 --> 52:18.080
(MAN SINGING)

52:22.040 --> 52:24.088
(FIDDLE PLAYING)

52:24.160 --> 52:26.845
(MEN YELLING)

52:27.720 --> 52:29.404
(MEN CHEERING)

52:40.320 --> 52:42.561
(CHEERING)

52:45.360 --> 52:46.361
(MAN WRETCH I N G)

52:47.280 --> 52:48.805
-(GUNSHOT)
-(ALL CHEERING)

53:01.160 --> 53:02.400
(ADA LAUGHING)

53:03.480 --> 53:04.606
ADA: And again!

53:05.840 --> 53:07.683
You should tell Ada to slow down.

53:07.760 --> 53:09.524
(SCOFFS) You think she'll listen to me?

53:09.760 --> 53:12.127
I've tried stopping her but
she's been drinking.

53:12.680 --> 53:16.082
She's been stuck in that little basement
for weeks, what do we expect?

53:16.160 --> 53:18.811
She's going off like a firecracker.
Oh, Christ, Tommy, please.

53:23.280 --> 53:26.409
Ada, come on, have a rest. Sit down.

53:26.480 --> 53:28.005
Come and look, Esme.

53:28.200 --> 53:30.089
Come and look at the family
you've joined.

53:30.160 --> 53:31.730
Come and look at the man who runs it!

53:31.840 --> 53:33.842
Chooses his brothers' wives for them!

53:33.920 --> 53:37.163
He hunts his own sister down like a rat,

53:37.240 --> 53:39.561
and he tries to kill his
own brother-in-law!

53:39.640 --> 53:40.641
Ada, that's enough!

53:40.720 --> 53:42.927
And now he won't even let
me have a fucking dance!

53:43.000 --> 53:44.923
- Ada!
- Not even at a fucking wedding!

53:45.000 --> 53:46.729
- Sit her down.
- Calm down, Ada.

53:46.800 --> 53:48.609
Ada, calm down.

53:50.200 --> 53:51.645
Holy shit.

53:51.800 --> 53:53.484
Water. Right.

53:53.560 --> 53:57.042
ARTHUR: Not now, Ada!
Bloody hell, you do pick your times!

53:57.800 --> 53:59.928
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

54:05.480 --> 54:06.811
ARTHUR: Let's go, let's go, let's go!

54:06.880 --> 54:09.326
Let's go! Whoa.

54:09.400 --> 54:11.084
Slow it up, nice and easy.

54:11.360 --> 54:13.886
Story of your fucking life.
Right, we're here.

54:17.360 --> 54:18.441
Come on.

54:20.480 --> 54:22.881
Nice car,john. How's she run?

54:22.960 --> 54:24.769
Yeah, beautiful, really smooth.

54:24.840 --> 54:27.571
Your sister's in there giving birth,
you're talking about the bloody car.

54:27.640 --> 54:29.210
Not much us men can do now, Pol.

54:29.280 --> 54:31.203
- Except go get drunk.
- Right, c'mon.

54:31.280 --> 54:32.281
One man should be here.

54:37.360 --> 54:38.691
You're right, Pol.

54:39.200 --> 54:40.531
Freddie should be here.

54:41.240 --> 54:43.242
Is that a heartbeat
I hear inside that chest?

54:43.560 --> 54:45.244
The truce lasts until sunrise.

54:46.000 --> 54:48.002
On my oath. Tell Freddie it's safe.

54:48.520 --> 54:49.726
Ada!

54:49.960 --> 54:50.961
All right, boys,

54:51.040 --> 54:52.644
let's wet this baby's head.

54:53.400 --> 54:54.640
(GROANING)

54:55.960 --> 54:57.450
Keep going. That's right.

54:57.600 --> 54:58.601
Push!

55:00.440 --> 55:01.885
(SCREAMING)

55:04.360 --> 55:06.169
I think it might be
the wrong way around.

55:06.680 --> 55:09.365
-(SCREAMING)
- I attended three sisters.

55:10.840 --> 55:12.922
- Yeah, I think you're right.
- We should move her forward.

55:13.040 --> 55:14.041
Come on, Ada.

55:14.840 --> 55:15.966
All right, come on.

55:17.560 --> 55:19.050
It's not long to go now, darling.

55:20.960 --> 55:23.247
Push, two, three!

55:24.000 --> 55:25.411
ARTHUR: To a beautiful wedding.

55:26.600 --> 55:28.011
I should go.

55:28.640 --> 55:30.165
- I should go soon.
- No, no, no, no.

55:30.240 --> 55:31.241
ARTHUR: No, you sit down.

55:31.840 --> 55:33.524
You don't want to be among women

55:33.600 --> 55:35.409
when there's a baby coming.
Have another.

55:35.480 --> 55:37.687
Do you think her husband will take
the same advice and stay away?

55:38.280 --> 55:40.567
JOHN: No, no, Freddie'll be there.

55:41.160 --> 55:42.810
Nothing'll keep him away.

55:42.880 --> 55:44.962
Tommy said it's all right
for him to be there.

55:45.360 --> 55:46.885
Isn't that right, Tommy?

55:47.000 --> 55:49.048
That's right. I'm all heart tonight.

55:49.120 --> 55:50.121
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

55:54.320 --> 55:56.243
(LAUGHS) You know what, john?

55:57.320 --> 56:00.290
I think it's that lovely barmaid,

56:00.360 --> 56:02.488
that pretty barmaid
that just walked out,

56:02.560 --> 56:05.291
that's made our brother go all soft.

56:05.480 --> 56:06.720
Drinks to that!

56:09.120 --> 56:11.043
(INAUDIBLE)

56:22.760 --> 56:23.966
Ada!

56:28.200 --> 56:29.725
Come on, open up!

56:30.160 --> 56:31.241
(BABY CRYING)

56:33.800 --> 56:34.801
There you go, love.

56:40.120 --> 56:41.770
He's beautiful.

56:46.000 --> 56:47.286
It's a boy, Freddie.

56:54.360 --> 56:56.522
It's a beautiful baby boy.

57:07.520 --> 57:08.760
There you go.

57:10.480 --> 57:11.925
Welcome to the world, Son.

57:14.680 --> 57:15.966
- Welcome.
-(DOOR KNOCKING)

57:16.120 --> 57:17.485
Open up, Police!

57:17.920 --> 57:20.241
-(DOOR SLAMMING)
- Freddie?

57:20.520 --> 57:23.126
You can't come in here!
There's a baby that's just been born.

57:23.200 --> 57:24.326
ADA: Freddie!
POLLY: There's a baby!

57:24.400 --> 57:26.209
Don't do this here.

57:26.360 --> 57:28.010
Don't hurt him! Freddie!

57:28.080 --> 57:30.970
You're hurting him! Leave him alone!

57:31.200 --> 57:33.168
You're taking me away from my baby.

57:34.600 --> 57:36.364
- Ada!
- Freddie!

57:36.600 --> 57:37.886
Ada!

57:46.160 --> 57:47.889
(MEN SINGING)

57:51.880 --> 57:54.611
You want me to open that champagne now?

57:54.760 --> 57:55.761
(DOORS SLAMMING)

57:56.920 --> 57:58.126
It's a boy.

58:00.920 --> 58:02.251
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

58:02.320 --> 58:04.163
ARTHUR: Oi, Polly! Polly!

58:04.800 --> 58:07.041
But the police came and
took his father away!

58:07.720 --> 58:09.882
Don't you dare look at me like that!

58:19.040 --> 58:20.041
(S PITS) You liar!

58:32.320 --> 58:33.321
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

58:49.440 --> 58:54.446
<i># Take a little walk to the edge of town
